<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-04T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-04T22:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/67: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-05T06:00:00+03:00">May 5, 1936—6
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 4—11:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>288. Nothing has happened since my 287 to alter views expressed then.
                                There is still some firing but much less than this time yesterday
                                and we are in no immediate danger.</p>
                            <p>Much appreciate your repeating to me message in your 185<note n="28" xml:id="d291fn28">See footnote 23, <ref target="#pg_259">p.
                                        259</ref>.</note> which is admirably worded.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>